PREAMBLE

The Common Sense License (CSL) is a pro-community, pro-worker
license designed to prevent the extraction of free labor from
open-source communities by large corporations, platform
monopolies, and entities with disproportionate economic power.

CSL protects:
    1. Free use for individuals, nonprofits, cooperatives,
       researchers, academics, public-interest developers, and
       small businesses;
    2. Mandatory reciprocity for large-scale commercial users
       who derive significant economic value from the Software;
    3. Community autonomy through transparent governance,
       enforceable audit rights, and anti-evasion rules;
    4. Rights of workers, contributors, and maintainers through
       ethical-use restrictions and labor-credit recognition.

If you profit significantly from the commons, you must
contribute proportionally back to the commons.

The precise terms and conditions follow.

---

TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. DEFINITIONS

1.1 “This License” refers to version 1.1 of the Common Sense License.
1.2 “Software” or “Program” refers to any copyrightable work
    licensed under this License, including source code, binaries,
    models, APIs, datasets, documentation, and derivative works.
1.3 “Use” includes running, deploying, hosting, modifying,
    distributing, embedding, integrating, or deriving economic
    or operational value from the Software.
1.4 “Small-Scale User” means any individual, nonprofit
    organization, cooperative, public-interest institution,
    educational institution, researcher, or business with annual
    gross revenue under USD $10 million, including subsidiaries.
1.5 “Large-Scale Commercial User” means any for-profit entity
    with annual gross revenue of USD $10 million or more,
    including any parent, subsidiary, affiliate, or entity under
    common ownership or control.
1.6 “Attributable Revenue” means revenue directly or indirectly
    generated through the use of the Software, including but
    not limited to product sales, SaaS fees, subscriptions,
    licensing, consulting, advertising, automation value, or
    labor displacement.
1.7 “Labor Contribution” means documented engineering, design,
    maintenance, security review, localization, community support,
    accessibility, or compliance work performed by paid employees
    and applied toward required contributions.
1.8 “Commons Fund” means any fund, foundation, or cooperative
    pool designated to support maintainers, contributors,
    infrastructure, security, audits, hosting, research, or
    community-benefiting work.

---

2. BASIC PERMISSIONS

2.1 You may use, study, modify, run, and distribute the Software
    for any lawful and ethical purpose, provided all conditions
    of this License are met.
2.2 No permission beyond retaining this License is required for
    Small-Scale Users, except for compliance with Sections 4, 5,
    and 7.

