4. CONVEYING VERBATIM COPIES

4.1 You may convey verbatim copies of the Software as you receive
    it, provided you retain all copyright notices and include
    this License with every copy.

---

5. CONVEYING MODIFIED VERSIONS

5.1 Disclosure of Modifications
    5.1.1 Clearly state that you have modified the Software.
    5.1.2 Include the date(s) of all modifications.
    5.1.3 Provide a description of the modifications sufficient
          to identify functional changes from the original Software.

5.2 Source Code Availability
    5.2.1 All modified source code must be made available under
          this same License to any recipient of the modified version.
    5.2.2 For modifications deployed in production, hosted, or
          otherwise accessed by end users (directly or indirectly),
          the modified source must be accessible publicly or via
          an approved Commons Fund repository, unless verified
          Community Contributions equivalent to 13.37% of Gross
          Attributable Revenue have been made and documented.

5.3 Retention of Notices
    5.3.1 Retain all original copyright, attribution, and license
          notices.
    5.3.2 Add your own copyright/attribution notice for your
          contributions.

5.4 No Workarounds / Anti-Evasion
    5.4.1 You may not evade these obligations through license
          splitting, sublicensing, technical obfuscation,
          inter-affiliate deployment, or deployment through
          intermediaries without compliance.
    5.4.2 Parent, subsidiary, affiliated, or commonly controlled
          entities are treated as a single entity when determining
          Large-Scale status or contribution obligations.

5.5 Procurement & Incentive Alignment
    5.5.1 Contributions and compliance must align with any
          procurement, sourcing, or corporate governance policies
          that incentivize transparency, ethical use, and
          public-benefit alignment.

---

6. SOURCE CODE AVAILABILITY

6.1 Requirement to Provide Source
    6.1.1 Any conveyed, publicly deployed, or commercially used
          version of the Software must be accompanied by the
          corresponding complete source code.

6.2 Method of Access
    6.2.1 Source code must be provided via a public repository,
          approved Commons Fund repository, or other reasonable
          access method.
    6.2.2 Large-Scale Commercial Users who wish to keep certain
          modifications private must provide documented Community
          Contributions equivalent to 13.37% of attributable
          revenue, approved by the maintainers or Commons Fund.

6.3 Compliance Enforcement
    6.3.1 Failure to provide source code, or failure to make
          adequate contributions if keeping code private,
          constitutes a license violation and triggers Section
          12 (Termination).

---

7. NO SUBLICENSING

7.1 You may not sublicense the Software under different terms.
7.2 All copies, modified or unmodified, must remain under this
    License.
7.3 Any attempt to relicense or bypass obligations through
    sublicensing, partnerships, or layered contracts will be
    treated as an anti-evasion violation and triggers Section
    12 (Termination).

---

8. OBLIGATIONS OF LARGE-SCALE COMMERCIAL USERS

8.1 Contribution Requirement
    8.1.1 Minimum of 13.37% of Gross Attributable Revenue
          generated through the Software; OR
    8.1.2 Equivalent contribution in verified Labor Contribution,
          valued at fully loaded employee cost; OR
    8.1.3 A hybrid combination of cash and Labor Contribution.

8.2 Destination of Contributions
    8.2.1 Contributions must be directed to:
        8.2.1.1 The maintainers of the Software; or
        8.2.1.2 A foundation designated by the maintainers; or
        8.2.1.3 A Commons Fund approved by contributors.

8.3 Mandatory Source Disclosure
    8.3.1 All modifications affecting functionality or commercial
          deployment must be made publicly accessible under this
          License unless:
        8.3.1.1 Verified Community Contributions equivalent to
                13.37% of Gross Attributable Revenue are made; AND
        8.3.1.2 Contributions are documented and approved by
                maintainers or the Commons Fund.

8.4 Anti-Evasion / Affiliate Aggregation
    8.4.1 Revenue shifting, shell restructuring, inter-affiliate
          transfers, subcontracting, or technical workarounds
          intended to avoid obligations are strictly prohibited.
    8.4.2 Parent, subsidiary, affiliated, or commonly controlled
          entities are treated as a single entity when
          determining Large-Scale status or contribution obligations.

8.5 Audit Rights & Governance
    8.5.1 Maintainers, contributors, or the Commons Fund may
          request independent third-party audits to verify
          compliance with contributions, source disclosure, and
          obligations under this License.
    8.5.2 Large-Scale Commercial Users must cooperate fully with
          auditors and provide access to relevant financial
          records, employee records, deployment logs, or any
          other information reasonably necessary for verification.
    8.5.3 A public comment period may be instituted prior to
          approval of contribution exemptions, adjustments, or
          governance decisions.
    8.5.4 Audit costs will be borne by the audited party if
          discrepancies exceeding 5% of reported Gross
          Attributable Revenue or Contributions are found; otherwise,
          costs may be borne by the requesting party.

8.6 Incentive-Fit Structures
    8.6.1 Contributions and compliance should incentivize
          alignment of corporate actions with the public-benefit
          purpose of the Software and reward transparency,
          ethical deployment, and community engagement.

---

9. REPORTING AND AUDIT REQUIREMENTS

9.1 Annual Reporting Obligation
    9.1.1 Large-Scale Commercial Users must submit a written
          report each year detailing:
        9.1.1.1 A comprehensive description of all commercial
                uses of the Software;
        9.1.1.2 A good-faith estimate of Gross Attributable Revenue,
                including a breakdown by business unit, subsidiary,
                affiliate, or product line that uses the Software;
        9.1.1.3 Detailed documentation of Community Contributions,
                including cash payments, Labor Contributions, or
                hybrid contributions, with supporting receipts,
                payroll records, or other verifiable evidence.

9.2 Independent Audit Rights
    9.2.1 Maintainers, contributors, or the Commons Fund may, at
          any time, request an independent third-party audit to
          verify accuracy of reports, revenue calculations, and
          compliance with contribution obligations.
    9.2.2 Large-Scale Commercial Users must cooperate fully with
          auditors and provide access to relevant financial
          records, employee records, deployment logs, or any
          other information reasonably necessary for verification.
    9.2.3 A public comment period may be instituted prior to
          acceptance of any contribution or audit adjustment.
    9.2.4 Audit costs will be borne by the audited party if
          discrepancies exceeding 5% of reported Gross
          Attributable Revenue or Contributions are found; otherwise,
          costs may be borne by the requesting party.

9.3 Record Retention
    9.3.1 Large-Scale Commercial Users must retain all records
          relevant to Software use, revenue attribution, and
          Community Contributions for a minimum of five (5) years.

9.4 Compliance Enforcement
    9.4.1 Failure to submit reports, provide access for audits,
          or maintain sufficient documentation constitutes a
          violation of this License and triggers Section 12
          (Termination).

9.5 Small-Scale Users
    9.5.1 Small-Scale Users, public-interest entities, researchers,
          and educational institutions remain fully exempt from
          these reporting and audit requirements.

---

10. EXEMPTIONS

10.1 Small-Scale Users, public-interest entities, researchers,
    and educational institutions are exempt from Sections 8 and 9.

---

11. ETHICAL USE RESTRICTIONS

11.1 The Software may not be used to:
    11.1.1 Conduct or support military, policing, intelligence,
           or surveillance operations;
    11.1.2 Violate internationally recognized human, labor,
           or environmental rights;
    11.1.3 Develop systems whose primary purpose is worker
           displacement, rent extraction, or speculative exploitation.

11.2 These restrictions apply to all Users, regardless of scale.

---

12. TERMINATION

12.1 Any violation of Sections 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, or 11 terminates
    your rights under this License automatically.
12.2 Rights may be reinstated upon curing the violation within
    30 days and receiving written confirmation from maintainers
    or governance representatives.

---

13. PRESERVATION OF FREE USE

13.1 Nothing in this License restricts non-commercial or
    small-scale use of the Software.

